<TITLE> DB arrests 'mobile tower thieves' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 18 (bdnews24.com)The Detective Branch of Dhaka Metropolitan Police have busted an organised gang that steals generators from mobile towers. They have stolen six expensive generators countrywide, police said. They used to pose as engineers of a mobile company and take off expensive generators from the towers for 'repair', said assistant commissioner of DB SM Murad Ali. Following their confessions, a Tk 25 lakh generator was recovered from Lucky Electronics, a shop at Bhogra Madhyapara of Gazipur on Wednesday night, he said. Some forged identity cards were also recovered from them. The arrestees are gang leader Raju alias Russell, Sabuj, Mizan, Liton, Alamgir, Shahidul, Hasan, Mizanur and Zakir. Raju told reporters at the DB office in Dhaka that he had taken to this profession six months ago with the help of a man called Salam. bd
